                                                                                             XOFs, PRFs, and hash functions with variable-length output like cSHAKE, KMAC, TupleHash,
                                                                                             and ParallelHash can easily be used to generate an integer X within the range 0 â‰¤ X < R, denoted
                                                                                             as 0..Râˆ’1 in this document, for any positive integer R. The following method will produce
